reviews.text:
The Federal Banquet  Restaurant located in North Point, Hong Kong is a nice Chinese Cantonese restaurant that serves good decent food of quality.

I had the pleasure of having lunch and dinner here last week with my auntie Lok.  The food here  is nicely done and  quite tasty, especially the roast quail during lunch.  The dim sum dishes here are vast and plentiful.  

For dinner, our friend Janet joined me, my mother and Auntie Lok.   We had everything seafood that  evening, and i must say, everything seafood was fresh and delicious. The lobsters were a little on the skinny side, but then,  most lobsters in Hong Kong are. The prawns were big and tasty.  The abalones was likewise.  The roast pork was great, roasted just right with  the right amount of fat. Thus, giving it the nice and moist texture, not dry and tough .  The roast chicken was out of this world, but then , most  of the roast chicken in Hong Kong are out of this world to me .

Both meals that day was exceptional to me, but then that could be because my auntie Lok knew 1 of the managers who catered to us.  

Regardless of wether you know  a manager or not, Federal Banquet  is a nice place to have a bite , be it morning tea, lunch, brunch,  afternoon tea or dinner.

Enjoy.
Food was tasty. Prices were reasonable.
A typical big & bustling Cantonese restaurant in the not-so-exciting North Point area. Food is average but price reasonable. Definitely not a place for romantic meal.
Good value for money morning and afternoon dim sum tea.
A good and spacious dim sum place in the area.
